# vtokenize — a Verbose tokenizer written in Verbose

Brick 1 of the self-hosting arc: the first piece of a Verbose compiler
written in Verbose itself. This recognizes the NEXT core lexeme at a given
position in a source string and classifies it, agreeing with the reference
lexer (`src/lexer.rs`) on classification and token boundaries.

## What it covers (this brick)

1. Token variants. A `Token` sum type carries the lexeme KIND plus its
   source span (start, len) or decoded value. Variants: Ident, Keyword,
   Num, Op, Eof.

2. Scanner position. A ScanState holds the source text and a byte position.

3. Skip spaces. Advance past ASCII spaces before reading a token.

4. Identifier / keyword run. Count the [a-zA-Z0-9_] run starting at a
   position whose first byte is an identifier-start byte.

5. Digit run. Count the [0-9] run starting at a position.

6. Decimal weight (10^n) and integer decode (Horner over the digit run).

7. Decode the decimal value of the digit run.

8. Two-letter keywords (if, or, of).

9. Three-letter keywords (let, and, not).

10. Four-letter keywords (then, else, rule, true).

11. Five-letter keywords (match, false).

12. Seven-letter keyword (concept).

13. Keyword code dispatch by run length: classify an identifier run as a
    keyword (numeric code) or 0 for a plain identifier.

14. Operator / punctuation classifier. Two-character operators (==, =>, ::,
    >=, <=, !=) are matched before the one-character ones (: , . + - * / %
    = < > ( ) { } [ ]).

15. Operator byte length (2 for two-char ops, 1 otherwise).

16. next_token: skip spaces, then recognize and classify the next lexeme.

17. classify: encode the next token's kind+detail as one observable number
    so the example compiles native and runs (driver / oracle hook).

18. token_len: byte length consumed by the next token (boundary check hook).

## Out of scope (later bricks)

- INDENT / DEDENT (needs a column stack and line-start state).
- String literals and @attributes (need escape handling and a sentinel scan).
- Comments (-- to end of line).
- A materialized token stream / list (the AST has no growable list yet).
